## Part 1: Feature Build (New Feature with Frontend + Backend Validation)

**Scenario:** A construction company client has requested a new feature — **Overtime Entry & Approval for Site Workers**.

Site managers need to log overtime hours for workers at the end of each day. The system must validate the entries before they're saved and before payroll processes them.

### What to build

An overtime logging screen where a site manager can:
- Select a worker (from existing employee list)
- Enter the date, number of overtime hours, and reason
- Submit for payroll processing

### Validation requirements

**Frontend validations (before submission):**
- All fields are required
- Overtime hours must be between 1 and 6 (company policy caps daily OT at 6 hours)
- Date cannot be in the future
- Date cannot be more than 7 days in the past (late entries not allowed)
- Reason must be at least 10 characters

**Backend validations (on the API):**
- All the same rules as frontend (never trust the client)
- No duplicate entry for the same worker + same date
- Worker must exist in the system
- Total monthly overtime for a worker cannot exceed 60 hours — reject if this entry would push them over

### Deliverable

- Working feature with both frontend form validation and backend API validation
- Proper error messages shown to the user when validation fails (frontend or backend)
- Clean, readable code — we will review it

